      "writtenOn": "2016-11-29T21:11:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So the problem is that, in the case of merges, we may follow the \"wrong\" branch and end up far earlier in the commit history than we meant to.  I think we have to always follow the first parent.  That\u0027s currently how Commit.Recurse() works, but I\u0027m not sure if I want to rely on that.  If we think that\u0027s okay, then we can use it.",
      "parentUuid": "f01d104e_b9b4b9b1",
      "revId": "67a3151613f24853ae8774d7cf827f3ed85b8daf",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f01d104e_3c2437d2",
